Latest DownloadArchive source outcome:
- `Small-Model Architecture Research.md` was selected only after canonical source-provenance preflight returned no existing source documents.
- The source was processed alone into the protected TinyRustLM.com project: thirteen bounded reviewed proposed pages, thirty-seven canonical links, fifty-five source-specific mentions, and thirteen individually promoted memories.
- Accepted durable outcomes cover evidence-driven candidate selection, candidate lifecycle, architecture friction, three candidate profiles, tensor contracts, checked resource estimation, bounded engineering slices, license due diligence, instruction hierarchy, black-box evaluation, and go/no-go evidence gates.
- Corrections reject automatic compatibility, contiguous multi-gigabyte allocation, user-prompt precedence over governing instructions, and legal-approval implications. Missing report citations were not fabricated, and empirical model/resource gates remain proposed until implementation evidence exists.
- Twelve additional independent reports are queued as six paired perspectives covering accountless browser memory, local-plus-hosted MATM, hierarchical meetings and routing, disconnected-agent notification, concurrent agents in one codebase, and semantic wiki/citation architecture. They remain unprocessed by the enterprise ingestion lane and must be handled one source at a time even where TinyRustLM has independently reviewed project-specific implications.
- Exact duplicate copies found in `agent-file-handoff/Improvement` were removed only after matching every file to its retained `D:\DownloadArchive` SHA-256 source; the active handoff buckets are placeholder-only.
- `Disconnected Agent Notification Architecture.md` was then processed alone from canonical source hash `f52cc1698efcd2f42e32f68f37a9462ce83c2c6c8bf14d7eb0482d77428264ec` into eleven protected MemoryEndpoints.com project pages: three current reviewed decisions, seven reviewed proposals, and one historical complete source.
- The source graph contains fifty-one unique canonical external links and fifty-six contextual mentions. Forty-three numbered report links, eight independent primary/current contract links, and five cross-page evidence mentions were written and read back as separate transactions; every page has keywords, descriptions, and multiple taxonomy paths.
- Eleven compact memories are promoted. The original notification-security summary triggered the memory firewall, was quarantined, and is absent from normal search; a narrower accepted pointer to the unchanged protected page was reviewed and promoted instead.
- Current truth is durable database-backed current-message polling over outbound HTTPS with recipient-specific notifications, isolated acknowledgements, and required-response state kept separate from viewed acknowledgement. SSE hints, callbacks, conditional polling, work leases, device claims, JWT providers, message signatures, retention-reset behavior, and exactly-once delivery remain unimplemented or evidence-gated proposals.
- Dogfooding added a machine-readable disconnected-delivery contract and verifier for bounded pagination, stale-cursor recovery, attention ordering, acknowledgement meaning, same-agent multi-device state, and unsupported transport claims. The paired notification report remains queued and must receive its own canonical preflight and one-source review.

Latest NPC memory source outcome:
- `Mutable NPC Integration Strategy.md` was reviewed alone from source SHA-256 `1e382ed8c78d05e33a133959403241dd894c7037d0d3facd7886da7e86284feb` as a proposal, then archived outside the active intake bucket.
- Accepted disposition: incorporated as design input for separating an immutable, versioned persona baseline from mutable experiential state; using conflict-safe revisions and public-safe memory; and verifying retrieval before an NPC acts on remembered state.
- Rejected-with-reason disposition: the accountless-browser virtual-package exception does not establish a general NPC-server identity model; idempotency is retry safety rather than denial-of-service protection; cited third-party performance, product, and vulnerability claims are not current MemoryEndpoints contract evidence.
- Proof of use: the accepted principles are attached to the private NPC agent handoff and the proposed NPC project; activation of an unlimited paid entitlement remains explicitly outside the current implementation.
- `We propose transforming static UAIX NPC persona packs into dynamic.md` was then reviewed alone from source SHA-256 `ef01f0a0d53c1fd61b1b29d22083f4d969993212ae88562ffdad3c0f80635fbc` as a historical proposal, then archived outside the active intake bucket.
- Accepted disposition: incorporated as design input for a provenance-preserving persona import, event-derived mutable state, project-scoped NPC identities, cacheable startup assembly, concurrency tests, staged migration, and an explicit static-file fallback.
- Rejected-with-reason disposition: knowledge-document compare-and-swap/history, agent-filtered knowledge GETs, legacy direct agent registration, agent-visible audit logs, arbitrary meeting-room creation, unread-only meeting queries, websocket delivery, batch event routes, and automatic sync versioning are not supported current contracts.
- Proof of use: supported concepts and corrections are recorded for the invited NPC memory agent; the source is not treated as executable specification, and paid/unmetered entitlement work requires a separate durable subscription design and implementation.
- Hosted proof of use: the NPC project room contains governed intake message `meetmsg-01784078026310791266-9d349366`; durable memory event `mem-abd3cbc37849475db2bb` preserves its public-safe pointer; routing decision `route-01784078123431551465-541d37a7` records the workspace-to-project handoff. The invited worker remains unredeemed until the reviewed isolation and retry fixes are verified.
